description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an experienced, motivated, compassionate and enthusiastic nurse with excellent communication skills to join the Specialist Palliative Care Team in the Ty Olwen inpatient unit.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are looking for outstanding individuals who can make a real contribution to patient care and their colleagues. Working as part of the multi-disciplinary team you will contribute to the holistic care and management of the patient with specialist palliative care needs by providing expert nursing care to patients and their carers within the specialist inpatient setting.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ideally you must have significant post registration experience. Ideally with experience of working in the acute setting, chronic diseases, palliative care or cancer care experience. You will have excellent interpersonal skills and be a true team player.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We highly recommend informal visits if you are considering a post.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Karren RobertsWard Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;karren.roberts@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01792 703412&lt;/p&gt;
